UNITED STATES of America, v. J & W MUSIC COMPANY, a partnership consisting of Hugh Johnson and Carl Walker, Claimant of Thirty-Six Slot Machines and Gambling Devices, etc. No. 14704. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. June 2, 1954. James W. Dorsey, U. S. Atty., J. Ellis Mundy, Asst. U. S. Atty., Atlanta, Ga., for appellant. Clinton J. Morgan, Rome, Ga., for ap-pellee.

Before HUTCHESON, Chief Judge, and BORAH and RIVES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon the authority of United States v. Five Gambling Devices, Labeled in Part “Mills” and Bearing Serial Numbers 593-221 etc., (United States v. Denmark) (United States v. Braun) 1953, 346 U.S. 441, 74 S.Ct. 190, the judgment in the above styled and numbered case is affirmed.
